race.comment: AMAHNI'S GIRL (1) is a leader who scored easily at the Gold Coast over 1800m before finishing a long neck second over 1805m at Eagle Farm. Jumps from a low gate and despite the hefty weight rise, she is well placed to win. STOICISM (2) won her Maiden as expected over 1800m at the Gold Coast and then was beaten 1L there in a 60 over the same trip. The extra metres suit and she can bounce back into the finish. TRUE FAIRY (3) hasn't been far away and may appreciate the longer journey. She puts in and her best would see her in the money. BORN TO BE ALIVE (5) stepped up to a staying distance here last time and missed a whisker from the front. Has to come back 740m, but he will race forward and deserves another win.
